<promed@promedmail.org>

[This article does not tell us the veterinarian had a high titer to rabies, as many veterinarians are vaccinated against rabies. It also does not tell us if he required PEP (post exposure prophylaxis).

However, with rabies in the area it is better to cast a wide net, erring on the side of caution, than to be to lax and have someone else bit. The campus did not indicate it notified the students and this could be problematic.

One has to wonder why the epidemiologist did not include the campus in the alert? - Mod.TG

