[4] Virginia: canine (fox), feline, human exposure
Date: Wed 8 Mar 2017
Source: Richmond Times-Dispatch, Associated Press (AP) report [edited]
http://www.richmond.com/news/virginia/fox-with-rabies-bites-elderly-woman-in-n-va/article_f3104ed3-c730-5f31-bb9e-aa8121f9d7ed.html


A fox that repeatedly bit a 71-year-old woman before trying to attack a couple and their cat tested positive for rabies and has been euthanized.

The 1st attack occurred [Mon 6 Mar 2017] in Fairfax County, when the fox bit the elderly woman on the arms, legs, and hands. The woman was badly injured but is expected to survive. The fox then traveled about a mile away and attacked a cat, whose owner was able to knock the fox out and put it into a cage.

