[The province of Ontario can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at http://www.healthmap.org/promed/?p=9368. Perth County can be seen on the map at http://tinyurl.com/km83uvt. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ

Some of these articles were great at mentioning pets need to have up-to-date rabies vaccinations. This is critical for your pet, and for your protection as well.

Large animals, such as cattle, horses, and others need rabies prevention vaccination as well. Many handle their animals on a regular basis, such as dairy animals, show animals, FFA (Future Farmers of America), 4-H, other school project animals, horses for riding or showing, all represent a means of joy, but also a means of exposure for humans. It is cheap insurance to vaccinate your animals, save their lives, and potentially yours.

Rabid animals are unpredictable as many of these articles show. Even if you are in an urban/suburban/city area, your pet still needs a rabies prevention vaccine.

Most all mammals are susceptible to the rabies virus. Build a wall between the virus and yourself by vaccinating your pets, regardless of their size or use. - Mod.TG]
